<br>
Spine Break (the poison) and Magic Resists are key elements in dropping these guys.  <br>
<br>
If a bard is rooted (Spine Break poison), then they cant run around spanking their drum and doing whatever the hell they do.  You can just beat the crap outa them since Rogues, even toe-to-toe, outdamage these freaks of nature.  Continue to Backstab/Frontstab till the mandolin playing pile of froot is on the ground.<br>
<br>
If you have MR, their lame damage songs really wont do anything to you.  The only annoying thing is if they get away from you, they will heal up fast and come back.  So just make sure you catch them off guard in the first place and make sure poison sticks <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulirintz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lirin TZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/27/02 3:00:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=577.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/ribbon_small.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard songs.</span><hr size=1> hehe, a rogue or a deul weilding monk trys to stand toe to toe with me ill eat you with DS.  i have more ac, hp, and haste.  <br>
<br>
once you land the root, start jousting for backstabs.  thats where bards get hurt, aginst anybody who can get big single hits.  be it 2hs or backstab. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=10458 >Liringlas Lookinglass</a><br>
